                            <comment id="13987748" author="alex.andrushchak" created="Fri, 2 May 2014 14:49:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This file content is extracted partially (epub30-nav.xhtml only)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14044591" author="werecow" created="Thu, 26 Jun 2014 11:54:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Quite possibly the same issue: I&apos;m not getting any content when I try to extract the plain text from epubs from this site:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://downloads.hindawi.com/journals/ddns/2013/508686.epub&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://downloads.hindawi.com/journals/ddns/2013/508686.epub&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14100033" author="ccoms" created="Sun, 17 Aug 2014 18:24:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can&apos;t extract any text from this file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14372000" author="tpalsulich" created="Fri, 20 Mar 2015 20:11:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tika 1.7 seems to extract information from the attached file. Can you confirm you&apos;re getting the expected results, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ccoms&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ccoms&quot;&gt;ccoms&lt;/a&gt;? You can grab the jar from &lt;a href=&quot;http://tika.apache.org/download.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://tika.apache.org/download.html&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14372976" author="ccoms" created="Sat, 21 Mar 2015 19:33:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was checked Tika 1.7 today - no, it&apos;s also dont work as expected &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Tika 1.7 can extract only some metadata, but not any char of ~850 kbyte of text, that contained in file. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tpalsulich&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tpalsulich&quot;&gt;tpalsulich&lt;/a&gt;, you can unpack file bad-parsed.epub with 7z archiver, many text files in *.xhtml format placed in folder \OEBPS. My system is: Windows 7, Java 1.8, russian locale.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16468483" author="glesialo" created="Wed, 9 May 2018 06:56:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I checked Tika 1.18 and the bug is still there. Most .epub documents are read incorrectly (either no content or only partial content). I looked inside some of those documents and I saw that the text is contained in several &apos;.htm&apos; files. The relevant Tika parser &apos;org.apache.tika.parser.epub.EpubParser&apos; doesn&apos;t detect &apos;.htm&apos; files. I think the bug could be solved by changing just one line:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;else if (entry.getName().endsWith(&quot;.html&quot;) || entry.getName().endsWith(&quot;.xhtml&quot;))&apos;&#160; -&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &apos;else if (entry.getName().endsWith(&quot;.html&quot;) || entry.getName().endsWith(&quot;.htm&quot;) || entry.getName().endsWith(&quot;.xhtml&quot;) || entry.getName().endsWith(&quot;.xhtm&quot;))&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16468588" author="gagravarr" created="Wed, 9 May 2018 09:24:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for investigating this for us &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=glesialo&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;glesialo&quot;&gt;glesialo&lt;/a&gt;. I&apos;ve added the &lt;tt&gt;.htm&lt;/tt&gt; pattern in a0ffec1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16559818" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Fri, 27 Jul 2018 14:18:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I cherry-picked these into branch_1x so they&apos;ll be included in 1.19.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
